<br>
I'm sending you this letter from &quot;Dark Age of Camelot&quot; in a sense, since that is the game I have been playing for a few months now. I really like it, but I miss you all and thought I would send this note to let you know what I am up to. Please feel free to write back! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Although I have played DAoC in all three of the realms there, Albion, Hibernia, and Midgard, I keep liking Hibernia the most. One of the reasons is I love playing a Lurikeen! They are so cute and cuddly. When I first went there I decided to try playing on the Guinevere server because it is a roleplaying server and I wanted to learn more about roleplaying. But a number of people from our RA guild had been playing in Hibernia on the Bors server, and they wanted to start a guild there. So have been playing on Bors. But I missed the roleplaying atmosphere of Guinevere. <br>
<br>
Finally after some soulsearching and a long talk with my husband I realized I was unhappy playing on the Bors server, so this week I moved back to Guinevere. <br>
<br>
My sister, who has been unable to get EQ to work right on her puter since Shadows of Luclin has started playing DAoC and we are in Hibernia on the Guinevere server and we want to learn to roleplay. Her character is Jeneve and my two characters are Acornie (soon-to-be last name Squash) and Mooneyan. If you ever come to DAoC we invite you to play in our small roleplaying group, which is not even a guild. I am playing as an anonymous benefactor of others, one who shuns the spotlight. I am looking for a roleplaying story to model myself on--maybe you know of one. We are independent players who keep a chatgroup open--that's a nice feature of DAoC, you can start a chatgroup even if you don't have a guild.<br>
<br>
I hope to hear from some of you and if you are ever in Hibernia, please look me up!<br>
<br>
*hugs* and as ever, Good Journey Friends!<br>
<br>
